sub_queries:
Generate a 2x3 grid of subplots with a figure size of 7x7 inches using constrained layout. All plots share a synthetic signal dataset: a 10-second duration signal sampled at 100 Hz, composed of a 4 Hz sine wave (amplitude 0.1) plus random noise (seed=0).

Row 1, Column 1 and Row 1, Column 2: Create identical line plots titled "Signal". X-axis: "Time (s)"; Y-axis: "Amplitude". Plot the time-domain signal.

Row 2, Column 1: Create a line plot titled "Magnitude Spectrum". X-axis: "Frequency (Hz)";
